Rye-grass experiment

Source: R/data.R
rye_grass.Rd

An experiment conducted to compare three different cultivars of rye-grass (Cropper, Melba, Melle) in combination with four quantities of nitrogen fertilizer (0 kg/ha, 80 kg/ha, 160 kg/ha, 240 kg/ha).

The experiment utilised two fields with each divided into three strips of land. Each strip consisted of four plots.

strip

A strip of land.

plot

A plot within the strip.

cultivar

The cultivars tested.

fertilizer

The quantitites of nitrogen fertilizer used in kg/ha.

weight

The total weight of dry mass after harvest.

perc

The percentage of water-soluble carbohydrate in the crop.

rye_grass

Format

An object of class edbl_table (inherits from tbl_df, tbl, data.frame) with 24 rows and 6 columns.

Source

Bailey, Rosemary (2008) Design of Comparative Experiments.
